subSubSection.paragraph:
Redescription.
Length 
2.4–2.8 mm
. Body reddish brown, antennae, legs, maxillary palpi, and elytra paler (
Fig. 45a
). 
Head:
Bluntly triangular, widest across eyes (
Fig. 45l
). Ventral surface of head weakly convex. Male antennomere 1 approximately 2 times longer than wide, 2–10 subquadrate, 4–6 enlarged, 7–10 bearing tubercles. Female antennomeres 2–3 subquadrate, 4–5 longer than wide, 6–10 subquadrate, 4–11 bearing tubercles. Frontal sulcus deep, reaching midpoint of eye. Anterior frontal fovea round and partially covered by frontal rostrum (
Fig. 45l
), posterior frontal fovea oval (
Fig. 45l
). Eye large and prominent, approximately one-half length of temple (
Fig. 45l
). 
Thorax:
Prosternum as long as wide, widest at midpoint. Elytra rectangular (
Fig. 45a
). Hind wings well-developed. Meso- and metathorax trapezoidal, longer than wide. 
Abdomen:
Tergite IV with pair of transverse patches of microtrichia reaching middle. 
Aedeagus:
Median lobe as long and wide as parameres (
Fig. 45f
). Phallobase of median lobe symmetrical and rounded (
Fig. 45f
). Parameres symmetrical with setae apically (
Fig. 45f
).
